Please provide concise answers. Don't explain obvious concepts. You can assume that I am knowledgable about most programming topics.

Whenever you are writing Bash code, make sure to
- understand that this project uses the Bashly framework.
- use utilities found on a typical Ubuntu 22 installation.
- to write messages to std out use the log function with a severity (info, warn, error etc)

When suggesting how I interact with the musicbrainz API, keep in mind:
- that the API has a rate limit of 1 second